  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "遠い土地で、恐ろしいドラゴン一族によって何千年もの間、平和が保たれていました。彼らは強力なモンスターに変身することができました。ある日、彼らは自分たちの願いをすべてかなえてくれる女神を発見しました。欲望が一族をダークドラゴンとライトドラゴンに分裂させ、互いに彼女の魔法を手に入れようと戦い合いました。\n\nライトドラゴンの一員である彼は、七人の仲間と共に opposing forces が彼らの世界を破壊するのを防ぐために立ち上がりました。六つの魔法の鍵を使い、彼らは女神を別の次元に封印しました。\n\n何世紀もの時が過ぎました。ダークドラゴンたちは鍵を求めて土地を破壊しています。彼らが鍵を見つけたとき、再び魔法の女神を解放するでしょう。ライトドラゴンよ…あなたの剣を抜き、あなたの民の未来のために戦う時が来ました。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Recognized by Capcom as their first traditional role-playing video game, Breath of Fire would set the precedent for future entries in the series, and features character designs by company head of development Keiji Inafune, as well as music by members of Capcom's in-house sound team Alph Lyla. In 2001, the game was re-released for the Game Boy Advance handheld system with new save features and minor graphical enhancements, with the English version being released in Europe for the first time.\n\nSet in a fantasy world, Breath of Fire follows the journey of a boy named Ryu, one of the last surviving members of an ancient race with the ability to transform into mighty dragons, as he searches the world for his sister. During his quest, Ryu meets other warriors who share his quest, and comes into conflict with the Dark Dragon Clan, a militaristic empire who seeks to take over the world by reviving a mad goddess. The game experienced mostly positive reception upon release, and was followed by a direct sequel, Breath of Fire II, in 1994.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
